  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of consulting with stakeholders (usually not involved in the creation of the IT architecture) is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Educate these stakeholders on the architecture;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Solicit feedback from them on the IT architecture;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide information to them on optimizations and other findings;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Clarify and define priorities moving forward.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This is the first step in preparing for the consultation:&amp;nbsp;define the objective of the consultation, starting with&#xD;
    the type (i.e. Business, Technical, or Operational).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Target Stakeholders&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The consultation&amp;nbsp;takes place in multiple fora, depending upon the target stakeholders involved. Once the objective&#xD;
    of the consultation is agreed, then identify the target audience; the stakeholders involved.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Business level&lt;/strong> - consult mainly with business&amp;nbsp;stakeholders and non-technical managers;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Logical / Technical level&lt;/strong> - consult mainly with technical stakeholders;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Operations&lt;/strong> (and&amp;nbsp;optionally maintenance) - consult with appropriate business and technical&#xD;
        stakeholders.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Each of these types of consultations will naturally have different objectives and focus, along with the set of&#xD;
    stakeholders involved.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Typically the objectives and focus for each type of consultation are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Business level&lt;/strong>&amp;nbsp;- discuss and agree business level optimizations or opportunities,&#xD;
        &lt;em>and&lt;/em> education and feedback on business processes, etc.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Technical level&lt;/strong> - discuss and agree technical level optimizations or opportunities, &lt;em>and&lt;/em>&#xD;
        education and feedback on technical solutions, etc.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Operations&lt;/strong> - discuss and agree operational requirements and constraints and practicalities of&#xD;
        proposed solutions, &lt;em>and&lt;/em> education and feedback on solutions, etc.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    All types clarify and define the priorities moving forward.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Actions are documented, assigned&amp;nbsp;and tracked.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
